# Go Coding Standards

> **Scope**: These rules apply to **new and modified code only**. Do NOT refactor
> existing code solely to fix legacy violations listed in the exemptions below.
> When modifying an existing file, apply the standards to the lines you touch —
> do not rewrite surrounding legacy code to comply.

## Import Organization

Group imports into TWO sections separated by a blank line:

```go
// ✅ GOOD
import (
    // Standard library
    "context"
    "fmt"
    "net/http"

    // Third-party and local
    "github.com/stretchr/testify/assert"
    "github.com/vcp-vsa-control-Plane/vsa-control-plane/core/datamodel"
)

// ❌ BAD - no separation
import (
    "context"
    "github.com/stretchr/testify/assert"
    "fmt"
)
```

**Import Aliases**: Use consistent, meaningful aliases. Avoid duplicate imports.

