## Testing Best Practices

### Use Dependency Injection

```go
func TestCreate_Success(t *testing.T) {
    mockStorage := database.NewMockStorage(t)
    mockHyperscaler := hyperscaler.NewMockServices(t)
    
    activity := NewActivity(mockStorage, mockHyperscaler)
    
    mockHyperscaler.On("CreateResource", mock.Anything).Return(nil)
    
    err := activity.Create(context.Background())
    assert.NoError(t, err)
    mockHyperscaler.AssertExpectations(t)
}
```

### Table-Driven Tests

```go
func TestOperation(t *testing.T) {
    tests := []struct {
        name   string
        input  Input
        expect Output
    }{
        {"case1", Input{Val: 1}, Output{Val: 2}},
        {"case2", Input{Val: 2}, Output{Val: 4}},
    }
    
    for _, tt := range tests {
        t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {
            result := Operation(tt.input)
            assert.Equal(t, tt.expect, result)
        })
    }
}
```

### Test Error Conditions

```go
func TestOperation_Error(t *testing.T) {
    mockSE := database.NewMockStorage(t)
    mockSE.On("Save", mock.Anything).Return(errors.New("db error"))
    
    err := activity.Save(context.Background())
    
    assert.Error(t, err)
    assert.Contains(t, err.Error(), "db error")
}
```

## Code Review Checklist

Before submitting:
- [ ] Imports properly grouped (stdlib / third-party+local)
- [ ] No cloud-specific imports in `core/`
- [ ] Context as first parameter
- [ ] All errors checked or explicitly ignored
- [ ] Type assertions use two-value form
- [ ] Dependency injection used for external dependencies
- [ ] Functions decomposed for testability
- [ ] Tests written for new functionality

> **Reminder**: This checklist applies to new and modified code. Legacy violations
> listed in the exemption sections above do not need to be addressed unless
> you are already refactoring the affected code.
